The key to understanding high CPU usage with WebRTC is the fact that it requires a browser to run. Current desktop apps use Electron, which is essentially a Chromium-based framework. When you download WebTorrent.desktop, you're essentially downloading a whole copy of Chromium (call it Google Chrome, if you want..).
&nbsp;
The code really just needs a cleanup so as to make it more efficient and lightweight. WebRTC is still too new.. but its potential to change the world is huge, and all the coding will be worth the effort.
